SIMPLE: roundly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roundly
<hw>Round"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a round form or
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Openly; boldly; peremptorily; plumply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He affirms everything <qex>roundly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Briskly; with speed.</def>
<rj><au>locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two of the outlaws walked <qex>roundly</qex> forward.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Completely; vigorously; in earnest.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Without regard to detail; in gross; comprehensively;
generally; <as>as, to give numbers <ex>roundly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In speaking <qex>roundly</qex> of this period.</q> <rj><qau>H.
Morley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roundness</ent>⟦br⟧
